As the attack and killings of innocent people continue in the North East by Boko Haram insurgents, the Arewa Consultative Forum (ACF) on Monday urged the Federal Government to review its negotiation strategy with Boko Haram insurgents and ensure that victims still in captivity of the sect, including Leah Sharibu and the Chibok girls are rescued. A statement by its National Publicity Secretary, Alhaji Mohammed Ibrahim Biu called on the government to intensify its rescue operations in order to assuage the fears of Nigerians of what may happen to those still in captivity. The ACF expressed shock and sadness over the killing of four aid workers including a woman by Boko Haram terrorists in Borno State on Saturday. The forum extended its condolences to the families of those executed and equally commiserated with the families of victims still in captivity. “It would be recalled that sometimes last year two female aid workers with International Committee of the Red Cross (ICRC) were abducted by the terrorists during an attack on the military base in Rann, Borno State, and were subsequently executed by the terrorists on the ground that the Federal Government (FG) failed to meet up some of their demands. “The recent action of the terrorists, to say the least, was callous, barbaric and inhuman and totally against the tenets of Islam and humanity. The killing is a clear desecration of Islam which preaches sacred inviolability of the individual, “the forum stated. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.